text: Mohammad Abdullah Mohammad Mustafa (born August 26, 1954) is a Palestinian economist and politician. He has been the prime minister of the State of Palestine and the Palestinian National Authority since 2024. Mustafa was the Chairman of the Board of the Palestine Investment Fund (PIF), Senior Economic Advisor to President Mahmoud Abbas and an Independent member of the Executive Committee of the Palestine Liberation Organization before becoming prime minister. He was also deputy prime minister and Minister of National Economy of Palestine. ==References== Category:Living people Category:1954 births Category:Prime Ministers of the Palestinian National Authority
